# Luxia Firmware Rules

## Startup Order (critical — do not reorder)
1. `sky_core_init()` — framework bootstrap
2. `sky_power_init()` — battery status available early
3. `sky_wifi_init()` — network
4. `sky_stepper_register()` — motor + battery guard hook
5. `sky_matter_init()` + `sky_matter_add_window_covering()` — protocol
6. `sky_ota_init()` — updates
7. `sky_sleep_init()` — idle timer last
8. `luxia_cmd_init()` — command module
9. Event subscriptions
10. `sky_core_start()` — starts all registered services

## Bridges (inter-component wiring in main.c)
- **Stepper → Matter**: `on_position_event` subscribes to `SKY_EVENT_STEPPER_POSITION`, calls `sky_matter_wc_update_position/status`
- **Matter → Stepper**: `wc_callbacks` (open/close/move_to/stop) call `sky_stepper_set_height/stop`
- **Power → Stepper**: `battery_motor_guard` hook on `BEFORE_MOVE` blocks motor when critical

## GPIO Pinout (Luxia PCB)
| Function | GPIO | Notes |
|----------|------|-------|
| Stepper IN1–IN4 | 17, 16, 4, 0 | GPIO 0 = boot mode, monitor |
| Battery ADC | 34 | ADC1, input-only |
| Wake button | 35 | input-only, pull-up |

## luxia_cmd Module
- Product-specific command handlers bridging custom API to sky_* components
- Command IDs: 0x01 calibration, 0x10 presets, 0x20 sequences, 0x40 diagnostics
- `luxia_cmd_init(motor_handle)` stores the motor reference for all handlers
